      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BING BING CHARM (4) continues to race well but is struggling to break through, placing at her last six runs. Last time finished 3rd over 312m at this track beaten 5.5 lengths (18.57) behind LANGLEY in a Grade 5 /MDN on June 21. Rates highly and will give a great sight. LANGLEY (8) has a strong record this journey here with two wins and a minor from five starts. Scored by 2.5 lengths last time (18.20) in a Grade 5 /MDN over 312m at this track. Looks one of the chances. OUR GIRL FRANKY (2) was safely held in tougher company last start at this track, but prior to that won by 1.5 lengths at this track (18.23) beating Dirty Dancing in a Grade 5 /MDN on June 14. Yet to miss the placings in seven runs from this box, including two wins. Expected to run well. SPORTSTER (1) has ability and finds the right scenario to bounce back.",
